'''Kabutozuka Kofun''' (兜塚古墳) is a {{ill|kofun|ja|古墳|1=Kofun|12=draft|12=draft}} located in {{ill|Sakurai, Nara|ja|桜井市|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Nara Prefecture|ja|奈良県|12=draft|12=draft}}. It has a {{ill|keyhole-shaped tumulus|ja|前方後円墳|1=Zenpokoenfun|1=Zenpokoenfun|12=draft|12=draft}} design and is Historic Site1 as a Sakurai City Historic Site.

== Overview ==

[[File:Kabutozuka Kofun (Sakurai), sekkan.jpg|thumb|250px|right|{{center|Carved {{ill|house-shaped stone coffin|ja|家形石棺|1=House-shaped Sarcophagus|12=draft|12=draft}} in the rear circular section}}{{small|Made of Aso welded {{ill|tuff|ja|凝灰岩|12=draft|12=draft}}, an ancient house-shaped stone coffin.}}]]

The kofun is constructed at the northwestern tip of a ridge extending west of the Asago settlement in the southern {{ill|Nara Basin|ja|奈良盆地|12=draft|12=draft}}. It has been subjected to grave robbery, and an excavation was conducted in 1954.

The mound is keyhole-shaped, oriented westward. It is built on a plattype, with small gravel (possibly {{ill|fukiishi|ja|葺石|12=draft|12=draft}}) and fragments of {{ill|cylindrical haniwa|ja|円筒埴輪|1=Cylindrical Haniwa|12=draft|12=draft}} identified on the surface. The burial chamber is a {{ill|pit-style stone chamber|ja|竪穴式石室|1=Vertical Pit-Style Stone Chamber|2=ja|3=竪穴式石室|4=zh|5=豎穴式石室|1=Vertical Pit-Style Stone Chamber|12=draft|12=draft}} located in the center of the rear circular section, aligned parallel to the mound's main axis. It was constructed using flat river stones, measuring approximately 3.7 m in length and 1.4 m in width, though much of it has been destroyed.

Some researchers suggest it may be a pit-style lateral entrance chamber due to the presence of a gravel spread on the east side of the stone chamber. Inside the chamber, a carved {{ill|house-shaped stone coffin|ja|家形石棺|1=House-shaped Sarcophagus|12=draft|12=draft}} made from Aso welded tuff (also known as Aso pink stone or Umamon stone) rests on a clay bed. The coffin measures about 2.1 m long, 1 m wide, and 1 m high. Its lid is rounded with minimal ridges, featuring two rope-hanging knobs slightly angled upward on each side—a style typical of ancient house-shaped stone coffins. Similar coffins made from Aso welded tuff are also found in kofun like the {{ill|Nogami Kofun|ja|野神古墳|12=draft|12=draft}} in {{ill|Nara|ja|奈良市|12=draft|12=draft}}.

Although the site was looted, excavations revealed grave goods, including ornaments (jade tubular beads, amber barrel-shaped beads, silver hollow beads, glass beads), iron arrowheads, and horse gear (gilt bronze decorative plates, apricot-leaf-shaped pendants).

The kofun is estimated to have been constructed in the late {{ill|5th century|ja|5世紀|12=draft|12=draft}} during the mid-{{ill|Kofun period|ja|古墳時代|12=draft|12=draft}}.

The site was Historic Site1 as a Sakurai City Historic Site in 2000.

== Mound area ==

* Total length: 40 meters
* Rear circular section:
** Diameter: 20 meters
** Height: 3.5 meters
* Front section:
** Width: 19 meters
** Height: 3.5 meters

The mound is built on a plattype measuring 48 meters east-west, 26 meters north-south, and 4 meters in height.

